PrecisAmendment (SCHEDULE No. 939) to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS which sets a Maximum Residue Limit on the amount of the herbicide "FENOXAPROP-ETHYL" that can be detected in milk, due to the possibility that livestock may ingest it from eating treated forage or crops.
